[h2 id=GeneralImprovements 
	" General Improvements
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	"This movie is 13.05 seconds (781 frames) faster than my previous one (
	(__wikiLink|href=/3444M|implicitdisplaytext=3444M)
	"). In general, I improved this run by using diagonal inputs and partner switching more frequently throughout the run and I only collected 1210 Studs, which is 450 Studs less than I collected in the previous movie.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=LevelImprovements 
	" Level Improvements
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=DeathStarEscape_2 
	" Death Star Escape
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"In the boss fight with Darth Vader, I lure him to a nearby pit and push him into it. But before his death cutscene starts, I purposefully run into the pit and die so I can lose 100 Studs. This saves time after the level ends when it counts all my Studs.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=TheTrenchRun 
	" The Trench Run
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Similar to what I did in Death Star Escape, I kill the boss and purposefully get shot by lasers in order to die and lose 20 Studs before his death cutscene starts.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Destiny_2 
	" Destiny
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"In the cutscene where Luke watches Darth Vader die, you still have full control of Luke. If you hold Right and fall into the pit, Luke will die but will respawn on the platform. But for some bizarre reason, if you push the other Luke into the pit at a specific time, the cutscene will end about 200 frames earlier than usual. 
	$LF
]div
